ninsd
-----

Ninsd is a little daemon which ask clients of the
local network for IPv6 adress and name. After these
data are collected the name server is updated and
the cleinets can be adressed by name.

Ninsd is to be installed on the same machine as the
name server and on the clients you must install
ninfod (https://github.com/yaegashi-ninfod)


radvc
-----

Radvc ist auf Clients rechner zu installieren die nur
mit radvd ihre IPv6 Adresse bilden oder bei den das
DHCP v6 nicht optimal unterstüzt wird.
Radvc has to be installed on the clients. Radvc
correct the file /etc/resolv.conf which will contain
the nameserver and the domain search lust offered by
radvd.

The daemon rdnssd which is provided by many Linux
distribution don't know at this time the domain search
list, this will be added on the next version. For now
you should use radvc.
